<section
  class="bg-surface border-y border-cream/[0.04] py-28 px-10 max-md:py-16 max-md:px-6"
>
  <div class="max-w-[1200px] mx-auto fade-in">
    <div class="section-tag">The Fork in the Road</div>
    <h2
      class="font-display text-[clamp(2rem,4vw,3.2rem)] font-extrabold leading-[1.1] tracking-tight mb-6"
    >
      In this race, standing still means <span class="text-red"
        >falling behind.</span
      >
    </h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-16 max-md:gap-6 mt-12">
      <!-- Consumer Strategy -->
      <div
        class="relative p-10 border border-cream/[0.06] rounded-sm overflow-hidden"
      >
        <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 right-0 h-0.5 bg-cream-dim"></div>
        <h3
          class="font-display text-[1.1rem] font-bold tracking-[0.04em] uppercase mb-5 text-cream-dim flex items-center gap-3"
        >
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="w-5 h-5 shrink-0 text-cream-dim">
            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><polyline points="12 6 12 12 16 14"/>
          </svg>
          The Consumer Strategy
        </h3>
        <p class="text-cream-muted text-base leading-relaxed">
          Wait for Microsoft, Salesforce, and Intuit to ship AI features into
          software you already buy. Copilot writes your emails. Einstein scores
          your leads. You feel like you're keeping up, <strong
            class="text-cream font-medium"
            >but so is everyone else. You're running just to stay in the same
            place.</strong
          >
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Builder Strategy -->
      <div
        class="relative p-10 border border-cream/[0.06] rounded-sm overflow-hidden"
      >
        <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 right-0 h-0.5 bg-red"></div>
        <h3
          class="font-display text-[1.1rem] font-bold tracking-[0.04em] uppercase mb-5 text-red flex items-center gap-3"
        >
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="w-5 h-5 shrink-0 text-red">
            <path d="M4.5 16.5c-1.5 1.26-2 5-2 5s3.74-.5 5-2c.71-.84.7-2.13-.09-2.91a2.18 2.18 0 0 0-2.91-.09z"/><path d="m12 15-3-3a22 22 0 0 1 2-3.95A12.88 12.88 0 0 1 22 2c0 2.72-.78 7.5-6 11a22.35 22.35 0 0 1-4 2z"/><path d="M9 12H4s.55-3.03 2-4c1.62-1.08 5 0 5 0"/><path d="M12 15v5s3.03-.55 4-2c1.08-1.62 0-5 0-5"/>
          </svg>
          The Builder Strategy
        </h3>
        <p class="text-cream-muted text-base leading-relaxed">
          Recognize that the collapse in development cost means you can build <strong
            class="text-cream font-medium"
            >proprietary software, AI agents, and automated workflows designed
            around your specific business.</strong
          > Things no competitor can buy off the shelf. Products you own. Margins you
          keep. This is how you run faster than the landscape moves.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
